    "This inconsistency can be disconcerting to novice users.",
    "Debate around LLMs and inclusion tends to focus on the biases inherent in these models (Schwartz et al., 2022).",
    "If the training data being used to generate responses are biased (and we know that it is), then LLMs naturally will reflect this bias in their outputs.",
    "This is obviously undesirable.",
    "Although many developers of LLMs are trying to fix this issue, training data are still focused on materials that are available in languages that are well-represented on the Internet, such as English or German, and that are produced in wealthy nations of the Global North."
